description.narrative:
A total of 10 countries and territories in the Eastern Caribbean area made progress towards the implementation of the Safe School Framework pillars. With UNICEF´s technical support, Ministries of Education across the region (i) developed instruments that facilitate disaster risk management actions at national and school level; (ii) built the capacity of teachers in DRR, EiE and resilience education; and (iii) students achieved enhanced capacity to be prepared in the event of disaster.
| Status:On-track | As-of Date:07/01/2020
